Not a single tiger was killed in Nepal in the last three years. However, the
illegal wildlife trade has not stopped. News of [poachers and traders being
arrested](http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/lucknow/Two-from-UP-held-in-
Nepal-with-tiger-skin-bones/articleshow/45972469.cms ) with tiger skins and
bones have not stopped in spite of the authorities claiming zero poaching.

